AGI - Mohamed Amra, the man evaded in the bloody assault on a van in the penitentiary of a French highway, has a long history of convictions for violent crimes begun when he was only 15 years old. Thirty-year-old of Rouen, in the north-west of France, known as "La Mouche" (Moscow), "it's very well known to the judiciary", told journalists the head prosecutor of Paris Laure Beccuau. He has close ties with organized crime, said another source, and he's suspected of ordering drug-related murders. Another source said that Amra manages its network of drug traffic, however none of its 13 previous convictions - for crimes ranging from armed robbery to extortion - was directly connected to the traffic of narcotics, said Beccuau, who is conducting investigations on the attack on the highway.
&nbsp;
From January 2022 he was detained in the prison of Evreux, in the northwestern region of Normandy, to conquer several convictions, including by association with criminals, extortion, robbery, armed violence and participation in an illegal automotive rodeo. The last sentence, for robbery, was pronounced only last week. At the time of his escape he had to face two new charges, one for attempted murder and another for complicity in a murder in Marseille, the French Riviera, the center of drug trafficking and gang violence.
&nbsp;
His lawyer, Hugues Vigier, told the broadcaster BFMTV to be "bewildered" by yesterday's events, adding to find "difficult to imagine" that his client could be implicated in "the actions of indiscriminate, dramatic, insane and unforgivable violence".<br> In an extreme attempt to defend his client, the suggested lawyer suggested "another possible explanation" for the attack: Amra was not released, but kidnapped for revenge.
&nbsp;
The 20 Minutes newspaper mentions a police source that, although Amra's position in the Marsigliese Malavita is apical, "it was not believed to be capable of such a high-profile operation".<br> Today Amra should have attended a disciplinary hearing after the guards had discovered that the bars of his cell had been partially segated, said prosecutor Beccuau. The French media reported that it would be put into isolation after the alleged evasion attempt, too recent to activate additional security measures.&nbsp;

